<br>
Now for 50$ I can have my name changed.  Now have I ninja looted a dragon piece and ruined my reputation? no.  Have I stolen someone's items after they asked me for a transfer? no.  Have I trained a whole group to kill them? no.  How about adding people to /ignore and now having them back with a new identity.<br>
<br>
But if I did I can just have my name changed and things will be forgotten.  Names carry so much in this game, it carries good things and bad things.  You know people that you just DON'T group with because of how bad of a player they are, well you put them on /ignore and they can be back for 50 dollars.<br>
<br>
I do not like the idea, but that is just me.  I dont like the fact that you can change your whole past for a price.  I think it should stay with you forever, whether you do good or bad.<br>
<br>
Now I guess you could repent upon what you have done, but I know of hardly anyone that would say sorry for the past.  That is just my point of view though. <p><div align="center"><img name="cyonsig" src="http://kassinova.homestead.com/files/cyonkarsig.jpg" width="550" height="190" border="0" usemap="#m_cyonsig" alt="">
