<br>
To address that issue a little, on the swapping servers.  I play on Legends.  As some may have heard, Stormhammer is very heavily overweighted toward level 60.<br>
<br>
I have a 60 wiz there, guilded in an *incredible* guild (it's non-raid, we're not ubers).  I'm a more casual player, who moved to legends in the hopes that the dynamic content would be worth it.  For the most part, it is..but being in the guild I'm in (Ascending) is what's kept me there.<br>
<br>
However, I started a BST twink a little while back, mainly for some off-time fun.  People on SH tend to create soloable classes for their twinks, so that we can actually play the character.  The number of low level characters on SH is pathetic to say the least.  Perfect case in point, my BST Dugal has been leveling in lake of ill omen...last night, during prime time, there were *FIVE* players in that zone...and 3 of them were there camping the howling stones key.<br>
<br>
I've put in for a /movelog for Dugal, to go back to my home server with him.  The only reason for this is so that I can get groups...I'll need to learn how to play my BST in groups before lvl 50, and that just can't happen on Stormhammer.<br>
<br>
So, those two lvl 54 beasts you've seen pop up on your server...if they came *with* their gear, they must have come from Stormhammer.  If that's the case, give them the benefit of the doubt. <p>Shizza Nidiot
